>Description:
At section 14, the procedure `start' builds a path with (current-path), but once inside `start', the current path has changed, so it now points to a system path, which is not the intention, so the database cannot be find and there is a permission error when run from a non privileged user.
>How-To-Repeat:
1. Copy and paste the code from Continue: Web Applications in Racket, section 14. A Persistent Model
2. Run the application from the command line
